<h3>Build a Solid Base</h3>
<p>An Associate's degree in General Studies provides an excellent, well-rounded base for students who want to pursue a Bachelor's degree or immediate employment. Students who plan on transferring to another university are encouraged to finish their Associate's to maximize the transferability of their credits.</p>
<h3>Degree Overview</h3>
<p><strong> </strong>The AS in General Studies degree can be taken entirely online. Students must complete 32 credits of required&nbsp;<a class="extLink" href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/catalog/2013-2014/Foundations.pdf">Foundations courses</a>(scroll to page 52) and additional courses to reach a total of 60 credits. Use our <a href="x33948.xml">course availability list</a> and the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/catalog/2012-2013/Interdisciplinary%20Studies.pdf">University Catalog</a> to check course availability and offerings or contact us today at (208) 496-1800.</p>
<p>In addition to the foundation requirements, students may choose one cluster of their choice.&nbsp;Talk to your&nbsp;<a href="x24404.xml">advisor</a>&nbsp;about online clusters.</p>
<h3>How Long will this Program Take?</h3>
<p>Our online degree program allows students the flexibility to finish their degree while balancing a busy life. Students can accelerate to graduation by taking courses year round, or take a semester off when needed. Students must complete the program within four years.</p>
<h3>What are the Courses Like?</h3>
<p>Online Courses at BYU-Idaho follow a similar format and have the same learning objectives as campus-based courses. Students should expect to interact with each other and participate in the learning model. <a href="x21934.xml">Learn more about BYU-Idaho courses online.</a></p>
<h3>Where do I Begin?</h3>
<p>Students who meet the <a href="x43410.xml">admission requirements</a> can apply to be directly admitted into an online degree program. These students will start by taking the online orientation course,&nbsp;<a href="x43378.xml">GS 111</a>. This is a one-credit course offered every block that prepares students to succeed online and charts a course to graduation. Pathway students who complete Academic Start do not need to take GS 111.</p>
